<li id="cite_note-129"><b><a href="#cite_ref-129" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCox2002">Cox, Richard (2002). <i>Encyclopedia of British Football</i>. Routledge. ISBN.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+British+Football&amp;rft.aulast=Cox&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard&amp;rft.au=Cox%2C+Richard&amp;rft.date=2002&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polymath"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=JKbb02bg6zYC&amp;vid=ISBN0714652490&amp;pg=PA15&amp;lpg=PA15&amp;sig=tUjKOwVSoViffVMjO49YDHgNNF0" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=JKbb02bg6zYC&amp;vid=ISBN0714652490&amp;pg=PA15&amp;lpg=PA15&amp;sig=tUjKOwVSoViffVMjO49YDHgNNF0" rel="nofollow">p. 15</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-130"><b><a href="#cite_ref-130" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFBrian_Viner2006">Brian Viner (2006-10-12). <a href="http://comment.independent.co.uk/columnists_m_z/brian_viner/article1218714.ece" class="external text" title="http://comment.independent.co.uk/columnists_m_z/brian_viner/article1218714.ece" rel="nofollow">"Sporting polymath is a full-time post for which only obsessives need apply: It is hard to get the head round the idea that one man excelled in so many sports"</a>. The Independent<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://comment.independent.co.uk/columnists_m_z/brian_viner/article1218714.ece" class="external free" title="http://comment.independent.co.uk/columnists_m_z/brian_viner/article1218714.ece" rel="nofollow">http://comment.independent.co.uk/columnists_m_z/brian_viner/article1218714.ece</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-10-12</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Sporting+polymath+is+a+full-time+post+for+which+only+obsessives+need+apply%3A+It+is+hard+to+get+the+head+round+the+idea+that+one+man+excelled+in+so+many+sports&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Brian+Viner&amp;rft.au=Brian+Viner&amp;rft.date=2006-10-12&amp;rft.pub=The+Independent&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcomment.independent.co.uk%2Fcolumnists_m_z%2Fbrian_viner%2Farticle1218714.ece&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Polymath"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>: "I read a book by Mick Collins called All-Round Genius: The Unknown Story of Britain's Greatest Sportsman. It is about a man called Max Woosnam, who...toured Brazil with the famous Corinthians football team in 1913... won an Olympic gold medal for tennis, played golf off scratch, scored a century at Lord's, and made a 147 break on the snooker table."</li>
</ol>
</div>
